    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Enhanced Detach Type Debug Output for Better NAS Message Analysis\n\n### Summary\nThe `dump_detach_type_xml()` function in the NAS IES module was not providing descriptive information about detach types during debugging. When analyzing NAS messages with `NAS_DEBUG` enabled, engineers could only see raw numeric values instead of meaningful detach type descriptions.\n\nThis change enhances the debug output to show human-readable descriptions for all defined detach types, making NAS message analysis more intuitive.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/DetachType.c`: Enhanced `dump_detach_type_xml()` to display descriptive text for switch off and detach type values.\n- Maintains existing XML format for compatibility with existing tools.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Enable NAS debugging by compiling with `NAS_DEBUG` flag\n2. Trigger a UE detach procedure\n3. Observe the NAS debug output for detach type information\n\nBefore fix:\n```\n<Detach Type>\n    <Switch off>1</Switch off>\n    <Type of detach>1</Type of detach>\n</Detach Type>\n```\n\nAfter fix:\n```\n<Detach Type>\n    <Switch off>1 (Switch off)</Switch off>\n    <Type of detach>1 (EPS)</Type of detach>\n</Detach Type>\n```\n\nThis enhancement helps network engineers and developers quickly identify the type of detach procedure being initiated without needing to reference the 3GPP specifications for numeric values.\n"
}